rs in medieval kappen who stood near the cart gazed at him and then at each other, and then one of them turned and glanced in a given direction. 'Have you —?' asked Krug. But they did not reply and looked once more at each other.

I must not lose my head, thought Adam the Ninth — for by now there were quite a number of these serial Krugs: turning this way and that like the baffled buffeted seeker in a game of blindman's buff; battering with imaginary fists a cardboard police station to pulp;